Race.SpecificTitle: City of Westwego -- 6.50 Mills - CC - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the City of Westwego, State of Louisiana (the "City"), under the provisions of Article VI, Section 27(B) of the Constitution of the State of Louisiana of 1974 and other constitutional and statutory authority, levy and collect a special ad valorem tax of six and one-half (6.50) mills on all the property subject to taxation in the City (an estimated $415,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for one entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2020 and ending with the year 2029, inclusive, for the purpose of paying salaries and benefits, including pension benefits, for Police Department personnel?
